      "span_text": "Lee et al.'s study [CITATION_2] reported that the most common allergenic foods were cow's milk and shrimp (7.0%), followed by eggs and mackerel (5.8%), peanuts and tomatoes (3.5%), wheat and crab (2.3%), and pork, peaches, and soybean (1.2%)."
